snippet.textDisplay: I still don't get why anyone would buy an over glorified chromebook for 900 dollars?! I know people are going to say its way more powerful than a chromebook. which it is. but you can't really do more with it than a chromebook. he even said so himself in the video. you're not going to be able to comfortably do any serious video editing on it. or play any triple A games on it. I doubt it will even run triple A games from 2 or 3 years ago on it. at least not without lowering the resolution or settings. two years ago I bought a windows pc for 700 bucks. and I've played everything from grand theft auto 5 to street fighter 5 arcade on it. and my laptop has an I core 7 (not 10th gen) 16 gigs of ram. 1 terabyte hdd to install my games on and a 128 ssd drive for windows apps. and I have even done video editing on it. honestly I would buy a chromebook with an I core 3 and 8 gigs of ram for like 400 bucks before I'd buy the new mac air. the best thing I can say about it is that looks good. but looking good isnt worth 900 bucks to me
